            <title>[KAFKA-13294] Upgrade Netty to 4.1.68 for CVE fixes</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-13294</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;netty has reported a couple of CVEs regarding the usage of Bzip2Decoder and&#160;SnappyFrameDecoder.&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Reference :&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/netty/netty/security/advisories/GHSA-grg4-wf29-r9vv&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;CVE-2021-37136 - https://github.com/netty/netty/security/advisories/GHSA-grg4-wf29-r9vv&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/netty/netty/security/advisories/GHSA-9vjp-v76f-g363&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;CVE-2021-37137 - https://github.com/netty/netty/security/advisories/GHSA-9vjp-v76f-g363&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Can we upgrade Netty to version 4.1.68.Final to fix this ?&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
